#studywithme  #스윗미 #공부
 
[더보기란]
📢 Time table
* Every day : 08:00~24:00(Live), 24:00~08:00(Recorded)
* 상태표시 : 상단 현재시각 옆에 빨간불 들어오면 Live, 없으면 녹화방송(식사 및 기타)
* 12시~13시(점심식사), 18시~19시(저녁식사)
* 정기휴무 : 토요일
* 새벽방송은 녹방
* 창문속 화면은 서울의 실시간 중계입니다.

📢 시험 및 기간
* 23년 2월부터 감정평가사 준비중 
* [박문각 감정평가사]에서 지원을 받아 온라인으로 학습하고 있습니다.
* 종종 화면에 노출되는 강의 저작권에 관한 사항은 [박문각 감정평가사]로부터 사전 동의를 받았습니다.

📢 사용가능한 명령어
✔️  출첵 명령어 :  출첵,  ㅊㅊ, 복귀, ㅂㄱ
✔️  퇴첵 명령어 : 퇴첵,  ㅌㅊ, 외출, ㅇㅊ
✔️ 입장 명령어 : 중간고사방, 기말고사방, 모의고사방, 입시방, 공시방, 고시방, 학교방, 샤워방,
                               공부방, 인강방, 학원방, 과제방, 독서방, 운동방, 휴식방, 식사방, 간식방, 꿀잠방
✔️ 명언 명령어 : 명언-1에서부터 명언-41까지 예)명언-7
✔️ 명령어는 한 타임에 최대 3개정도만 해주세요. (도배는 타인에게 방해될수 있어요)

📢 information for foreigners
✔️ Hi, I am ziho in Korea. let’s study hard together!
✔️ I prepare for the exam once a year. If I pass the exam, I will be qualified to evaluate
      all real estate value in Korea.
✔️ Please chat during breaks, excluding commands and greetings.
✔️ commands : in, out, meal, study, break, back

📢 Product
✔️ 지워지는 볼펜 : 프릭션(4색 멀티 0.38mm, 노크존 0.7mm, 노크존 우드 0.7mm)
✔️ 지워지는 형광펜 : 프릭션(라이트, 라이트 네츄럴) 
✔️ 샤프 : 펜텔 그래프1000(+ain샤프심)
✔️ 컴퓨터 : LG 올인원
✔️ 스피커 : 미디플러스 MI3 II 3인치
✔️ 키보드, 마우스 : 로지텍 K380s, M350s
✔️ 계산기 : fx-9860g3
✔️ 독서대 : 셀프제작(가로 80cm)
✔️ 책상 : e-smart
✔️ 의자 : 시디즈 T50

📢 '열품타'를 운영하고 있습니다. 주20시간/주40시간
       - '공부하는지호'로 검색
       - 자세한건 커뮤니티 [열품타 공지]글을 참고해주세요.

📢 기타 내용
✔️ 출첵, 퇴첵 확인이 필요하신 분은 ‘좌측 상단의 시청기록-실시간 채팅’란에서 가능.
✔️ 채팅창 열어놓고 하시는분은, 불편한 채팅이 올라올시 '개인차단'기능을 이용하세요.

✔️ 나이, 성별 비공개
✔️ 악의적으로 반말, 비속어, 비아냥 거리시는 분은 바로 숨김처리합니다.
✔️ 과도한 친목으로 번질수 있는 인스타, 줌 등의 공유는 금지합니다. 

✔️ 디데이 적용을 원하시는분은 하루 전 업로드된 라이브에상에 댓글로 시험일/회차를 남겨주세요.
✔️ 노트북 배경화면은 강의 저작권 보호를 위해 사진으로써 연출한 것입니다.
✔️ 학습시간 시작과 끝에는 학교종이 울려요.
✔️ 채팅은 쉬는시간에 봐요.
✔️ 지호의 아침 지각벌금 : 누적 8000원

📢 문의
✔️ 인스타그램 : study.ziho
✔️ 메일 : study.ziho@gmail.com
✔️ 데스크테리어 제품 환영

📢 제작에 도움주신분들
✔️ 노래 - [아판뮤직] "바램" ARTIST : 박지윤, 이진헌 :  https://youtu.be/e0njles7ggI
✔️ GiGAeyesLiveTV : https://www.youtube.com/@GiGAeyesLiveTV(협의완료)
✔️ 지니어스 웹개발자 Mr.화해
✔️ 나눔뮤직 - https://tv.naver.com/v/13595048
✔️ ASMR은 무료파일을 직접 편집하였습니다.

S5.description:
⬇️⬇️ Links, schedule, and more information down below! ⬇️⬇️

Welcome! Come join for some motivation and accountability! Here we follow the 50/10 Pomodoro method, where we work for 50 minutes and then take a 10 minute break to chat, relax, craft and play puzzles! (we're obsessed with jumble words...)

I am a physics PhD student in my second year at the University of Auckland. My PhD is purely theoretical and computational, so I do lots of coding. My research looks at gravitational wave physics in relation to supermassive black holes and the future Laser Interferometer Space Antenna.

I did my undergraduate and masters in the UK, where I grew up, and then moved to New Zealand for my PhD. I now do purely research and don't take any classes, but I do teach some!

📚 أهمية "Study with me" 📚

نظام "Study with me" يوفر بيئة تفاعلية ومحفزة للدراسة. من خلال الانضمام لجلسات دراسية مشتركة، يمكنك:

تعزيز التركيز: البيئة المشتركة تساعد على تقليل التشتت وزيادة الإنتاجية.
تحفيز الإلهام: رؤية الآخرين يعملون يمكن أن تكون دافعًا قويًا لمواصلة المذاكرة.
بناء الروتين: الالتزام بمواعيد محددة للدراسة يساهم في تنظيم الوقت.
الدعم المتبادل: مشاركة التحديات والنصائح مع زملائك تساعد على تخطي العقبات.
📖 بنذاكر بتقنية بومودورو 50/10! 📖

تعتبر تقنية بومودورو 50/10 من أفضل الطرق لتحسين إنتاجيتك في الدراسة. تعتمد على:

50 دقيقة تركيز: خصص 50 دقيقة للدراسة بتركيز تام. اجعل هذه الفترة خالية من المشتتات.
10 دقائق استراحة: بعد كل 50 دقيقة، خذ 10 دقائق للاسترخاء. يمكنك القيام بتمارين بسيطة أو شرب كوب من الماء.
لماذا تعمل هذه الطريقة؟

زيادة الإنتاجية: يساعد التناوب بين التركيز والاستراحة في تعزيز القدرة على التحصيل.
تجنب الإرهاق: الاستراحات القصيرة تمنحك الطاقة للاستمرار.
تحسين التركيز: فترات العمل الطويلة تجعل عقلك أكثر استجابة واستعدادًا للتعلم.
جرب تقنية بومودورو 50/10 اليوم وراقب كيف ستتحسن نتائجك! 🌟
مستنينك معانا

S15.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

📌 Study Stream Rules
🔹 Stay Focused → Keep messages relevant to studying.
🔹 Be Respectful → No hate speech, insults, or spamming.
🔹 No Distractions → Avoid off-topic conversations or personal stories.
🔹 No Self-Promotion → Do not share links or advertise anything.
🔹 Keep It Clean → No inappropriate language or content.
🔹 Respect Privacy → Do not share personal information.
🔹 Follow Host Instructions → Listen to moderators and follow rules.
🔹 No Flooding → Avoid excessive messages or emoji spam.
🔹 Stay Encouraging → Support each other positively!

Frequently Asked Questions
Q: What's your name?
A: I go by Sunnie.
Q: Where do you live?
A: South Korea.
Q: How old are you?
A: I prefer not to share my exact age.
Q: What are you studying for?
A: I'm preparing to become an IT officer at another agency.
Q: What study method do you follow?
A: I use the Pomodoro technique – 60 minutes study, 10 minutes break!
Q: Can I chat during the study session?
A: No (Sorry about that! It might distract others from their studies).

Schedule & Updates: I usually study 8–10 hours daily (except Sundays), beginning between 7–9 AM Korean time, with breaks for meals and rest. On Sundays, since it's the weekend, I start later.

💖 Support the Stream:
👍 Like, Share & Subscribe if you're enjoying the content!

Hi, everyone! I'm Sunnie, living in South Korea.  
My name is similar to Sunnie, and I chose this name because I want to study with you all in a cheerful and bright way! 😊
I used to work as an IT officer for the Korea Army, but I decided to leave.  
Now, I’m studying again to become an IT officer at another agency.
I may not be extraordinary or remarkable, but I am someone who takes one step at a time toward my goals every day 
Honestly, I used to choose to do most things
 *alone*.
 But earlier this year, I started studying with others and realized for the first time how much synergy and joy it brings to study *together*.  
Studying can sometimes be challenging and lonely, but let’s go on this study journey *together*!😊
